cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a new approach to policy search for Markov decision processes (MDPs) and partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs), which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves transforming the problem into an equivalent POMDP with deterministic transitions, which could also fall under robotics (cs.RO) or control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses theoretical results and sample complexity bounds, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
